## ERROR — Push Blocked

Both push paths return HTTP 403:

1. Local git proxy:
   $ git push -u origin claude/wizardly-bell-1iew0k
   remote: Permission to lntkhoi1998/meso-tracker-collector.git denied to lntkhoi1998.
   fatal: unable to access 'http://127.0.0.1:46523/git/lntkhoi1998/meso-tracker-collector/':
   The requested URL returned error: 403

2. GitHub MCP (create_or_update_file / push_files):
   403 Resource not accessible by integration

Root cause: The GitHub App installation token for this session lacks
`contents: write` permission on lntkhoi1998/meso-tracker-collector.

Fix required (one of):
  A. Grant the GitHub App write access in repo Settings → GitHub Apps →
     grant "Contents: Read and write", then re-run:
       git push -u origin claude/wizardly-bell-1iew0k
  B. Manually cherry-pick the two local commits above onto the remote branch.

